==English==

===Etymology===
Formed through analogy with the effect of a [[shotgun]] blast, which contains many small pellets.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|head=[[shotgun]] [[sequencing]]}}

# {{label|en|genetics}} A [[DNA]] [[sequencing]] technique in which a large number of small fragments of a long DNA strand are generated at random, sequenced, and reassembled to form a sequence of the original strand.
#* {{quote-journal|passage=In '''shotgun sequencing''' of genomic DNA, fragments of a genome are sequenced and computationally reassembled to determine the genome of an organism|author=Selene K Swanson|coauthors=Michael P. Washburn|page=719|year=2005|title=The continuing evolution of shotgun proteomics|journal=Drug Discovery Today}}

